7. Glossary for Beginners (English)
IDOR (Insecure Direct Object Reference): Manipulating object identifiers (e.g., page IDs) to access unauthorized resources.

SQL Injection (SQLi): Inserting malicious SQL code into a query to manipulate the database.
XSS (Cross‑Site Scripting): Injecting malicious scripts into trusted websites.
Reflected XSS: Script is reflected off the server in an immediate response (e.g., in search results).
Stored (Persistent) XSS: Script is permanently stored on the server and served to all users (e.g., in a comment).
Event Handler: JavaScript code that runs in response to user actions (like clicking or mousing over an element). Examples: onclick, onmouseover, onerror.
URL Manipulation: Changing parameters in the URL (like page numbers) to test for vulnerabilities.

8. Tools Used (English)
Browser (Firefox/Chrome): View source, test payloads, navigate manually.

Developer Tools (F12): Inspect elements, check console for errors.

Burp Suite / OWASP ZAP (optional): Intercept and modify requests (not required for this lab).

